<p>You can do even more complex navigation and move forwards/backwards where necessary, meaning you donâ€™t need to keep moving up through your command history to find the right directory ever again (or keep those little pockets of brain energy remembering where that darn log file is)!</p>

<p>pushd accepts directories as parameters too, itâ€™ll take parameters and switch your current directory whilst pushing it onto the stack, useful if youâ€™re working with shell scripts:</p>

